@*<div class="textblock">
    TxDOT’s recommendation for downtown freeways and Interstate 45 North is the most influential recommendation for Houston’s freeways since the 1950s. 
TxDOT and its partners deserve credit for a bold plan to fully modernize downtown Houston freeways and enhance mobility.
However, review of the preliminary schematics reveals numerous points of concern which could compromise the ability of the new freeway system to meet current and future needs.
</div>*@
@*<div style="color:red; font-weight: bold; padding-bottom: 10px;">UPDATE SEPT 28, 2015: TxDOT has recently posted updated schematics on the project web site. This analysis will be updated in early October.</div>*@

@*<div class="bold">Updates resulting from July 22 and September 4, 2015, meetings with TxDOT</div>*@


<div class="updateItem">TxDOT placed updated schematics online for the inner-loop part of the project in May 2016. This was the second update, after the original release in April 2015 and the first update in September 2015.</div>



<div class="updateItem">The September 2015 update was a huge improvement over the original plan, and the May 2016 update provided another big improvement to the design.
    See the status of the <a href="#status-september-concerns">September 2015 concerns</a> and the  <a href="@Url.Action("analysis_sept_2015")">September 2015 detailed list</a>, and the status of the <a href="#status">original problem list items</a>.
</div>
<div class="updateItem">
    I'm pleased to report that my list of concerns continues to shrink and I now have only four items of concern relating to design, and three ideas for consideration.
</div>

<div class="updateItem">I appreciate TxDOT's efforts to refine the design to make it the best that it can be.</div>

<br />


