<div class="bold"><span>Other Analysis of TxDOT's Plan</span> </div>

<div class="updateItem">In March 2016, the blog <a href="http://purple.city">Purple City</a> posted a detailed <a href="http://purple.city/2016/03/10/a-better-plan-for-the-downtown-ring/">alternate plan</a> for the downtown freeway complex.
    Purple City has many excellent ideas, but it was too late in the process to make the kind of wholesale changes in the Purple City plan.
    I summarized the benefits of the Purple City plan in this <a href="@Url.Content("~/images/plan-analysis/Plan-comments-20160319.pdf")">document</a>, but it appears that none of the Purple City ideas can be implemented.
</div>

<div class="updateItem">
I also prepared this <a href="@Url.Content("~/images/plan-analysis/downtown-i45-option-large.jpg")">map</a> of a potential relocation of the IH 45 main lanes to create space to bring managed lanes through downtown. This option was not formally studied, although it may have been rejected very early in the process. 
    It is now too late to consider this option, but I think this would be the only way to create  a north-south corridor of managed lanes through downtown, assuming the Pierce Elevated will be removed.
</div>